The Plateau Chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party at the end of its 85th State Executive Committee (SEC) Meeting in Jos on Saturday, resolved to zone its governorship seat for 2023 to the Central Senatorial Distinct of Plateau state. The State Executive committee (SEC) after extensive deliberations on issues of urgent importance within the Party and the State as well as preparations for winning Elections come 2023, the SEC resolved that Plateau Central should produce the governorship candidate of the party during the 2023 election in the state. The Publicity Secretary of the party John Akans in a signed 6 points communique which itâ€™s copy was made available to Saturday Independent, said SEC Commends the efforts of the State Leadership of the party and other various organs of our great party: the Caucus, the National Assembly members, the elders forum and the structure of the Party at the ward, local government and zonal levels. According to him, SEC Commends the commitment of the State working committee ( SWC) under the Chairmanship of Hon Christopher Adukuchili Hassan for uniting and repositioning the PDP ahead of the 2023 general Election, and for the victory recorded at the last by-election of Jos North / Bassa Federal Constituency and Pankshin South (state)constituency respectively. Consequently, SEC charges all Party members across the State to work hard to ensure victory in 2023 general Election as they haveexpressed confidence in the ability of the State working committee (SWC) to lead the party to win all seats starting from the house of assembly to the Governorship seats. Similarly, SEC strongly condemns the incompetence, insincerity, corruption and insensitivity of the Lalong- led APC administration in the state, resulting in untold hardships, daily killings and increasing insecurity in the State. The communique noted with delight that Plateau people and indeed Nigerians are at this moment looking up to the Peoples Democratic Party with great hope for solutions to all the predicaments this present administration has caused. It therefore urges all party members to remain resolute in the vision and mission of the party to Rescue and Rebuild Plateau State. He added that in sequel to this, Plateau central Senatorial zone through Solomon Bulus Maren applauded and appreciated the SEC for the confidence, trust and the opportunity given to the zone to produce the next Governor of the State.